Unorg. Fed. Terr. (1802-04-24)

1802/04/24 -> 1804/03/26

Georgia ceded to the United States all territory south of North Carolina and Tennessee, east of the Mississippi River, north of 31 degrees north latitude and west of the present limit of Georgia. The area became unorganized federal territory.

(Paullin, 83; Van Zandt, 100; Terr Papers US, 5:142-143)
